page.title: 05River Test Estuary Housing
page.content: It was North of Millbrook Road & West of & including the T.A.V.R centre. It is a residential area. The houses were mainly old 1930s with a few modern ones here & there. The houses were mainly semi_detached with a few terraced & a few detatched. There were no bungalows or blocks of flats. The houses were mostly made of brick & pebbledash. The people look after their houses very well. Many houses had had alterations such as window replacements. The gardens were also looked after very well. Millbrook Road was busy. The other roads were quiet. The area has no problems except the occasional smell of tobacco from the B.A.T. factory and sewage smells.
